@startuml
title Next.js Build Failure From SDK 1.6.0 (Before Fix)
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #6D4C41
  LifeLineBorderColor #8D6E63
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
  ParticipantBorderColor #5D4037
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFE0B2
}
skinparam defaultFontName Consolas
autonumber

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "Next.js Compiler\n(Webpack/Turbopack)" as Compiler #BBDEFB
participant "@xylex-group/athena\ndist/index.js" as SDK #FFE082
participant "loadGeneratorConfig()" as Loader #FFCCBC
participant "Dynamic import expression\nimport(`${moduleUrl.href}?cacheBust=${Date.now()}`)" as DynImport #EF9A9A
participant "Module Resolver" as Resolver #E1BEE7

Dev -> Compiler : next build / next dev
Compiler -> SDK : Parse SDK dependency graph
Compiler -> Loader : Parse reachable exports
Loader -> DynImport : Contains runtime template-string import
Compiler -> Resolver : Try to resolve dynamic import context
Resolver --> Compiler : No resolvable module candidates
Compiler --> Dev : Module not found: Can't resolve <dynamic>

note right of Compiler
Failure happens at compile time, before app runtime.
Generator code was bundled into dist/index.js,
so Next analyzed it even when generator APIs were not called.
end note
@enduml
